comRegisterServer            package:rcom            R Documentation

_I_n_i_t_i_a_l_i_z_e _t_h_e _C_O_M _s_e_r_v_e_r

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     This function registers the COM server at runtime. It is called
     automatically when the package 'rcom' is loaded.

     Technically, this will register the class factory in the system,
     so calls to 'CoCreateInstance()' from client applications will
     succeed.

     _Remark: The type library will be loaded on demand later on_

     'comUnregisterServer()' is used to unregister the class object
     (class factory) again.

_U_s_a_g_e:

     comRegisterServer()

_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

_A_u_t_h_o_r(_s):

     Thomas Baier

_S_e_e _A_l_s_o:

     'comUnregisterServer', 'comRegisterRegistry'

